# Docker build context for apps/api — flyctl treats the Dockerfile's
# directory as context (apps/api/), so paths here are relative to that.
# Exclude anything the builder does not need: editor state, local build
# artefacts, test coverage, dev-only tooling. Goal is a fast upload to
# Fly's remote builder and a cache that invalidates only on real source
# changes.

# VCS metadata — worktree pointer file or full .git dir.
.git
.gitignore

# Local build outputs.
bin/
dist/
*.test
*.out
coverage/
coverage.*

# Editor + OS clutter.
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Env files — never bake secrets into an image.
.env*
!.env.example

# Lint config is container-irrelevant (golangci runs in CI, not the image).
.golangci.yml

# Dev-only docs + wrappers.
README.md
Makefile
scripts/

# Tests — `go build ./cmd/...` never reaches them; omitting shaves the
# context upload and keeps the remote build cache stable across test-only
# changes.
**/*_test.go
